What is the role of the "proof" in the `migrate_completeimporttransaction` command?

The "proof" in the `migrate_completeimporttransaction` command is a verification mechanism that ensures the validity and integrity of the cross-chain import transaction. The proof is generated on the asset chain and is then extended to the target chain proof root, allowing the transaction to be completed and verified on the target chain.
migrate_completeimporttransaction importTx Takes a cross chain import tx with proof generated on assetchain and extends proof to target chain proof root
